\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4270034 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12201098\charrsid2837000 How often did you used to have a bath?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3486081 FP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12201098\charrsid2837000 Every Friday night. And if it was - and if it were hot in summertime, well of course we'd - go and take a - a dive then, in tin bath.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4270034 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12201098\charrsid2837000 When you used to get out of the bath did you have clean clothes to put on?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3486081 FP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12201098\charrsid2837000 Every time. All change.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4270034 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12201098\charrsid2837000 Can you tell me where the family had their meals?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3486081 FP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12201098\charrsid2837000 Yes, we all had it in - in the - what they call the kitchen,
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4270034 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12201098\charrsid2837000 You always ate there, you didn't sort of move into the front room?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3486081 FP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12201098\charrsid2837000 
Oh no. Front room they always used to keep that, there were nobody allowed in only just - if we had somebody - come like you know visiting. But - as for us having us meals - meals we always had it in - in the kitchen.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4270034 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12201098\charrsid2837000 So your mother used to cook in the kitchen as well?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3486081 FP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12201098\charrsid2837000 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4270034 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12201098\charrsid2837000 Can you describe to me the way she cooked, presumably it would be a coal fire with coal oven?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3486081 FP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12201098\charrsid2837000 Oh it was coal - it were a coal fire, them days. Because we used to have - well, there weren't electricity then. In houses.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4270034 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12201098\charrsid2837000 No gas either?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3486081 FP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12201098\charrsid2837000 No gas, it used to be - paraffin. Hang up lamp in - middle of room.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4270034 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12201098\charrsid2837000 What time did the family have breakfast?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3486081 FP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12201098\charrsid2837000 Well - we had to have us breakfast - when were all - when we were all going to school like,
 we'd all to have had us breakfast by - half past eight. And - on us - then we used to have to get ready and get - off to school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4270034 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12201098\charrsid2837000 So usually - your dad was on shift work so sometimes he could be there and sometimes he couldn't, but apart from your dad
 usually was everybody there for breakfast?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3486081 FP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12201098\charrsid2837000 
Was was all there for breakfast. Oh no getting away through it if - they only used to shout breakfast ready - if we - out and - in yard you know, and we were all then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4270034 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12201098\charrsid2837000 So your dad would be the only one who was away, how would he manage for his breakfast would he take stuff to the pit?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3486081 FP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12201098\charrsid2837000 
Well - when he went to - when - in them days, they - they didn't used to bother with much breakfast because it used to like - what they call - rift on 'em you know, 
when you - go into work with a full stomach. They used to have - happen - two slices of flatten bread, something like that you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4270034 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12201098\charrsid2837000 But he'd take that with him to have down the pit?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3486081 FP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12201098\charrsid2837000 And - no, he'd have that for his breakfast before he went, jus
t two slices, no - no bacon like you know. We had plenty because we used to keep us own pigs. And - it always used to rift on you when you - with 'em being crouched you know as a miner. And it used to - all rift on 'em and - they'd take two - well - they'
d take two slices of - of bread and fat and - and a quarter - quart of cold water. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9331050\charrsid2837000 
And not boiled, it's what they used to get this here water - from - well he were working in Galloway's, Galloway's pit, they called it, at South Heeley, and - he'd - they used to get it out of what they called Freakler Bridge troughs. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12201098\charrsid2837000 And it were pure - as clean as anything All - from a spring.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4270034 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12201098\charrsid2837000 This was supposed to be particularly good water?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3486081 FP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12201098\charrsid2837000 It was good water. Fill their bottles and fill their glass - their quart b
ottles full of water. They all used to fill it there, that lived at - that lived at Brierley to get to that pit.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4270034 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12201098\charrsid2837000 What would you usually have for your breakfast, what would you have to eat and what would you have to drink?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3486081 FP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12201098\charrsid2837000 Well we - mother'd - of
 course mash tea like you know for us and - we'd - have bacon because - I mean to say we had plenty, 'cos - we used to - feed - feed one or two pigs for ourself besides - me dad used to sell - a little.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4270034 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12201098\charrsid2837000 You'd have a cooked breakfast every day then would you?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3486081 FP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12201098\charrsid2837000 No, not every morning 'cos we didn't feel like it sometimes you know as kids.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4270034 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12201098\charrsid2837000 But a cooked meal would have been there if you'd wanted it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3486081 FP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12201098\charrsid2837000 Oh if we'd have wanted it we could have had it, as some of us wanted it and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4270034 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12201098\charrsid2837000 It wasn't just something that you had on Sundays?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3486081 FP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12201098\charrsid2837000 
Oh no, no, no. I daresay it would be for a lot of 'em in them days but of course we was breeding us own and - and - we used to get 'em killed at - at }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9331050\charrsid2837000 Kenyon\rquote s}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12201098\charrsid2837000 , where I went to work. And they used to salt 'em - they used to sell - well - we'd - two - we'd two big }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9331050\charrsid2837000 cellars}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid12201098\charrsid2837000  to that house, and - two big stones down there and of course me dad - used to - carry 'em down there, then Joe Kenyon used to come and salt 'em for us.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4270034 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12201098\charrsid2837000 What about midday meals, lunchtime, would everybody come home for lunch?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3486081 FP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12201098\charrsid2837000 
Well - at dinnertime - we - it - it were all got ready for us, at dinnertime, for us that were going to school like and - if me dad were - me dad were working like, on days, well he didn't - didn't get home then wh
ile about three. And - me mother'd make - would make his dinner separate. See. 'Cos I mean to say - a - a dinner as has been stood at - well I couldn't eat one, not like that. That had been stood on waiting for about a couple of hours.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4270034 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12201098\charrsid2837000 So all the children that were at school then would come home for a midday meal?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3486081 FP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12201098\charrsid2837000 Oh yes, it used to be a race home for dinner, you can bet on that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4270034 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12201098\charrsid2837000 This would be another cooked meal would it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4270034 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12201098\charrsid2837000 What you mean, at tea time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4270034 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12201098\charrsid2837000 At lunchtime, what would you have for your lunch usually?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3486081 FP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12201098\charrsid2837000 Well - there were just what we call - a breakfast, a dinner, and then at tea. At tea we -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4270034 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12201098\charrsid2837000 What did you have at dinnertime then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3486081 FP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12201098\charrsid2837000 Well we used to have potatoes and - and - carrots and all such as that like you know
 Turnips. All mashed - mashed up like you know. And then -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4270034 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12201098\charrsid2837000 So you'd have vegetables and not meat at lunchtime?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3486081 FP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12201098\charrsid2837000 And -ad - oh we'd plenty of meat, aye, there were plenty of meat. Aye, plenty of meat it weren't same price as what it is now. You cou
ld get -
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4270034 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12201098\charrsid2837000 Was it unusual that you had so much meat?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3486081 FP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12201098\charrsid2837000 Oh yes. Y}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5070914\charrsid2837000 es.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2837000  }{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12201098\charrsid2837000 W}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5070914\charrsid2837000 e}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12201098\charrsid2837000 
 could get - we could get plenty of meat. And if we - if - if you if you was going to be short of money, well - she'd go and - lift a piece of bacon down and - or ham and cut som
e - some off of that and - oh we were never - we were never clemmed for meat, wed always plenty.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4270034 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12201098\charrsid2837000 So lunchtime would be sort of twelve o'clock, half past twelve?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3486081 FP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12201098\charrsid2837000 Half past twelve. Then back to - then we used to go - get off back to school at about five minutes past one, something like that you know.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4270034 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12201098\charrsid2837000 The evening meal would be your tea would it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3486081 FP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12201098\charrsid2837000 That's right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4270034 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12201098\charrsid2837000 What time would you eat that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3486081 FP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12201098\charrsid2837000 Well - about five o'clock it'd be.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4270034 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12201098\charrsid2837000 What you usually have for tea?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3486081 FP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12201098\charrsid2837000 Well sometime
 we'd have some toast or - an egg and - all like that you know. It often used to be - well I used to like toast. And - and I like it yet as far as the goes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4270034 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12201098\charrsid2837000 This was the last meal of the day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3486081 FP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12201098\charrsid2837000 No, we - we used to have supper. Well sometimes it'd be - we'd have a drink of milk and - a bun or something like that, you know,}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2837000  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12201098\charrsid2837000 - I mean to say - they didn't use to - slip off to shops same as they do now. They used to - me mother used to bake }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9331050\charrsid2837000 them}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12201098\charrsid2837000 . And - she - I've - well I've seen as many as - thirteen o
r fourteen loaves or on a table when we've - when we've comed home, that me mother's baked. I remember her - she used - we never used to buy nowt, we - my mother never used to buy - used to - by bread. And that - that's the reason I don't like - I don't l
ike bought }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9331050\charrsid2837000 bread}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12201098\charrsid2837000  now. I call it borrow bread. Which it is, i}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5070914\charrsid2837000 t }{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12201098\charrsid2837000 doesn't taste like - home made }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9331050\charrsid2837000 bread}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12201098\charrsid2837000 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4270034 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12201098\charrsid2837000 Was there any sort of special food that you had on Sundays or any other days?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3486081 FP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12201098\charrsid2837000 Oh aye, we used to - it used to be a - a tin of salmon like you know,
 and it weren't same price as what it is now you know. About six bob - we could get a tin of salmon then for ninepence.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4270034 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12201098\charrsid2837000 That was a sort of special treat to have a tin of salmon?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3486081 FP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12201098\charrsid2837000 Well no no, well I think we got salmon and salmon - you know - we 
used to get tired on it, I - I used to do. Sometimes I'd - I'd do a jelly - I'd do a jelly for myself when I got bigger like you know. Of course jellies wouldn't take much making - making they used to be - sell 'em in packets and they were only a penny a 
packet was jelly and they - they do a basin full then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4270034 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12201098\charrsid2837000 Were the meals better that you had on Sunday then or not?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3486081 FP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12201098\charrsid2837000 Well - well - not - not so much difference, 'cos - my mother always kept a good table. She always used to say - let 'em have some foo
d while they're young and they'll be able to carry on - 'til - when they get growed up, and I think that's reason as I'm living to - be my age at turned eighty.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4270034 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12201098\charrsid2837000 You said that your mother made the bread, did she make her own jam?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3486081 FP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12201098\charrsid2837000 Oh, jam, strawberry jam and raspberry jam. And another thing that she used to make I've just forgotten.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4270034 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12201098\charrsid2837000 Raspberry vinegar?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3486081 FP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12201098\charrsid2837000 Was some raspberry vinegar. But you never see - oh, sorry.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4270034 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12201098\charrsid2837000 Did she used to bottle fruit?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3486081 FP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12201098\charrsid2837000 No, she never used to - bottle fruit, 
we used to - she used to make jam like you know and - put it in jars. We used to have a big - what they call the - copper pan, a big copper pan. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9331050\charrsid2837000 
It'd hold - oh it must have held about two gallon, 'cos it - me mother couldn't lift it off. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12201098\charrsid2837000 Me mother couldn't
 lift it off of the fire. We used to cook that, 'cos fire range that we had in house - it wasn't as big as what we }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5070914\charrsid2837000 had}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12201098\charrsid2837000 
 in the wash house where we used to go and get bathed. And - 'course when - they'd to keep - going and stirring it round when she wanted i
t lifting off well then - me dad had to come - and - lift it off then. 'Cos mother couldn't - and me mother was big woman but she couldn't lift that off. Well of course me dad always was - }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9331050\charrsid2837000 you
\rquote re}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12201098\charrsid2837000  not fit to lift it off, you'll be scalding yourself.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4270034 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12201098\charrsid2837000 You also used to grow a lot of vegetables in the garden, did she have any ways of preserving them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3486081 FP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12201098\charrsid2837000 
No, we never used to - preserve many - vegetables. Because I mean to say we - we had vegetables near - going, cabbages, and the - the autumn cauliflowers, we had them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4270034 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12201098\charrsid2837000 You had fresh vegetables all the year round?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3486081 FP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12201098\charrsid2837000 All the year round. And of course -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4270034 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12201098\charrsid2837000 Did she dry things like sage and parsley and whatnot, did she do that?
\par 
