\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3486081 FP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12201098\charrsid2837000 Yes. I remember m}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6359751\charrsid2837000 e Uncle John, and he died with d}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12201098\charrsid2837000 ropsy.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4270034 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12201098\charrsid2837000 How old would you be then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3486081 FP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12201098\charrsid2837000 I would be about
 - twelve, I'd be about twelve. And he left me - left me his watch. And it were a - a watch with - and it had a miner with a pick in his hand and he }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6359751\charrsid2837000 were}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid12201098\charrsid2837000  going like that all time. Picking away. I'd had it - I had it years and years that watch. And he - he died with }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10446766\charrsid2837000 dropsy}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid12201098\charrsid2837000  and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4270034 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12201098\charrsid2837000 Was he living at your house at that time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3486081 FP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12201098\charrsid2837000 
Aye, he were living with us then, he died, aye, had drop - with dropsy. But you never hear tell of anybody dying with that now, dropsy. And - he - he was a miner as well, he used to work at same pit as what me dad did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4270034 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12201098\charrsid2837000 How old would he be when he died, do you know?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3486081 FP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12201098\charrsid2837000 He'd be about fifty-six, something like that. Aye, be about fifty-six.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4270034 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12201098\charrsid2837000 Did you go to his funeral?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3486081 FP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12201098\charrsid2837000 Yes, oh aye, we went to - we all went to funeral. All family. Oh yes. Even - youngest. We all went to funeral, he was buried -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4270034 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12201098\charrsid2837000 Was this a sort of village tradition?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3486081 FP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12201098\charrsid2837000 He's buried at - he's buried in Brierley churchyard.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4270034 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12201098\charrsid2837000 Was this usual, if anybody died did the whole family used to go, now it's quite frequent that children don't go to funerals?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3486081 FP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12201098\charrsid2837000 
Well we all went. We all went. Every - we all went, walked it there. And it - at that time - they never used to have - a hearse for to take 'em you know. They used to - carry 'em. From home. To -
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4270034 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12201098\charrsid2837000 So the coffin would be carried from where you were living?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3486081 FP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12201098\charrsid2837000 Aye, to church, to Brierley church. And it's nearly a - it's - it's - a - it's a last walk.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4270034 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12201098\charrsid2837000 Did people used to wear mourning clothes then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3486081 FP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12201098\charrsid2837000 Yes, they used to - every - there used to be a lot of black worn. But now they don't - seem to - bother with it but -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4270034 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12201098\charrsid2837000 So then your mum would be dressed in black would she?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3486081 FP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12201098\charrsid2837000 She were dressed in black, and me dad. And - there was some more with - if you were winter - well if you - ay
e, it was summertime. And we used to - get black - suits like, you know, dark suit, not same as they are now. Dark, more dark like you know. Aye.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4270034 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12201098\charrsid2837000 So you had a dark suit?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3486081 FP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12201098\charrsid2837000 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4270034 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12201098\charrsid2837000 So you wore that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3486081 FP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12201098\charrsid2837000 And - in them - and in them days they - w
hat they used to - they used to have - funeral cards then. But you don't see many of them now. That seems to have all gone out.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4270034 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12201098\charrsid2837000 You didn't buy clothes specially for the funeral?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3486081 FP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12201098\charrsid2837000 Well -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4270034 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12201098\charrsid2837000 It just was lucky you had a dark suit?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3486081 FP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12201098\charrsid2837000 Yes, aye. But me mother - me mother always - me mother had one.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4270034 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12201098\charrsid2837000 Did they have sort of mourning bands? Black armbands?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3486081 FP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12201098\charrsid2837000 Aye, they used to - they - it's - now then, I believe it were armband that I had on my coat. Mm. Now you've mentioned that. Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4270034 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12201098\charrsid2837000 But black was the sort of accepted colour that one wore at funerals?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3486081 FP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12201098\charrsid2837000 Yes. Of course they don't bother with so black - with black so much now.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4270034 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12201098\charrsid2837000 Were you taken out visiting neighbours, friends, relations, it would have been quite an undertaking with a family this size?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3486081 FP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12201098\charrsid2837000 
Well - not all together we didn't always - like that. Sometimes we'd be - happen a couple you know 'cos - me mother, well - she used to think well - people have got families of their own, they don't want in - they don't want - bother with other }{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10446766\charrsid2837000 folks's}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12201098\charrsid2837000  kids. That's what she used to think.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4270034 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12201098\charrsid2837000 Did your mother go visiting, you mentioned earlier that she went visiting relatives occasionally?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3486081 FP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12201098\charrsid2837000 Aye, but - only - when you want fruit time. That's only time that she used to spend more time going - visiting.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4270034 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12201098\charrsid2837000 What about friends and neighbours?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3486081 FP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12201098\charrsid2837000 Oh -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4270034 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12201098\charrsid2837000 Did she have friends outside the family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3486081 FP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12201098\charrsid2837000 Oh she'd friends, she'd plenty of - plenty of friends. Aye.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4270034 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12201098\charrsid2837000 And neighbours, did she go into neighbours houses?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3486081 FP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12201098\charrsid2837000 And - s
he was a woman of the sort that - they even used to - they even used to come if anybody died they used to come and fetch her to go and - you know, to lay - what they call lay 'em out. And she'd plenty of work without doing that, but she wouldn't she would
n't refuse anybody.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4270034 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12201098\charrsid2837000 She was sort of one of the accepted people in the village who did this?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3486081 FP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12201098\charrsid2837000 
Mm. Well it - everybody knew her. Knew me mother. Aye. They did that. Aye, she were a well - she were a well known - woman in Brierley were mother. Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4270034 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12201098\charrsid2837000 So your mum would take you out visiting neighbours, would your dad take you out in this way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3486081 FP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12201098\charrsid2837000 Oh many a time for - well - I've gone with me - I've gone with me dad - out - out - have a trip.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4270034 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12201098\charrsid2837000 Would this be out to visit friends and relatives or not?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3486081 FP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12201098\charrsid2837000 Well more than out it were more for business than out.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4270034 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12201098\charrsid2837000 So if you were going out visiting other }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10446766\charrsid2837000 people\rquote s}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12201098\charrsid2837000  houses it was usually with your mum?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3486081 FP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12201098\charrsid2837000 Yes. Mm. Mm. Well me dad - well - he were no one for - going visiting like you know, he used
 to say, I've plenty to do at home. Without - without going visiting. But it were quite a change for me mother to get - out like you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4270034 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12201098\charrsid2837000 How frequently would you think she would go? Would this be once a week?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3486081 FP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12201098\charrsid2837000 Well - happen about - happen about twice a week. That'd be - that'd be after sunset Were that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4270034 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12201098\charrsid2837000 Did you used to go out with your mum when she went shopping?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3486081 FP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12201098\charrsid2837000 Well - we had to do.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4270034 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12201098\charrsid2837000 To help her carry it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3486081 FP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12201098\charrsid2837000 But - she used - they used to do a lot of shopping at Barnsley. And o
f course - me Uncle John, that were her brother - that lived with us, he used to go - he used to and }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10446766\charrsid2837000 meet her}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12201098\charrsid2837000 
 - down at Curworth Station. Then me dad'd - he'd happen - meet her, he happen - set off - in time - and go and meet her about - meet 'em about Shafton. And that's - a good mile from where - from where we lived. Aye.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4270034 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12201098\charrsid2837000 So quite frequently when your mum went shopping she'd take one child with her to help her carry?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3486081 FP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12201098\charrsid2837000 No, she used to go on her own, shopping. Well sometimes she'd take our Sarah w
ith her but - when - when they got working, when they got working and - they used to when they called - went to service, working for gentry, well they couldn't go then you see No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4270034 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12201098\charrsid2837000 The times you went out just with your dad, these were usually times whe
n you were going out to sell that stuff that you'd grown in the garden? Did you go to football matches or anything like that with him?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3486081 FP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12201098\charrsid2837000 No, never used to bother with football in them - not - 'cos we - I mean to say we'd - we'd got to look after stuff 
at that time, in summertime and - well we - it in winters we could go and - and have a game of football or - you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4270034 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12201098\charrsid2837000 But you didn't just go out with your dad on your own just for pleasure?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3486081 FP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12201098\charrsid2837000 Oh no. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4270034 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12201098\charrsid2837000 Did he take you for walks or anything like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3486081 FP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12201098\charrsid2837000 Well sometimes he'd take us up to common, but it were only for to do some work. Sir as I say, when he was going -
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4270034 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12201098\charrsid2837000 You used to go to chapel three times a days, was this just the children or would your mum go with you then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3486081 FP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12201098\charrsid2837000 Me mother always used to go - at - afternoon and night.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4270034 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12201098\charrsid2837000 Buy the mornings were just a session for the children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3486081 FP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12201098\charrsid2837000 But - she were - morning my father was - of course she couldn't go - she couldn't go on a morning because she - busy with dinner.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4270034 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12201098\charrsid2837000 But 
apart from the occasional trips to relatives and friends who were mostly living in the same village I suppose, you didn't go out from home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3486081 FP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12201098\charrsid2837000 Oh no, we didn't go -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4270034 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12201098\charrsid2837000 Did you ever manage to get away on holiday or did you go out on sort of trips to the seaside or anything like this?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3486081 FP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12201098\charrsid2837000 Seaside, it - the only seaside ever we used to get to - we - what - were to Askon. Askon pond. And -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4270034 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12201098\charrsid2837000 How did you used to get there, did you go on a family trip?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3486081 FP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12201098\charrsid2837000 We used to - get Dick Walton from Moorethorpe
, and his wagonette. And we always - all used to go - and have a good day there. Sometimes there'd be - a woman called - well - now then - Rhodes, Mrs Rhodes. And she'd go and take their Charlie. And take their Charlie with us.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4270034 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12201098\charrsid2837000 This was something arranged from the village then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3486081 FP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12201098\charrsid2837000 
Yes. Aye, they used to arrange it with their two selves, and - get Dick Walton from Moorethorpe to - to come - to come and fetch 'em, and it were - we used to be as ha- as - and when we got there they used to buy us a pear
, and then we'd have a ride on boat, at - at - at Askon, and we - we used to right enjoy it more than - more than what they do now when they go to seaside kids.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4270034 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12201098\charrsid2837000 How frequently would this happen, would this be perhaps once a year?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3486081 FP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12201098\charrsid2837000 Only once a year. Aye. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4270034 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12201098\charrsid2837000 Did you ever manage to get away for a holiday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3486081 FP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12201098\charrsid2837000 Oh no. No. I mean to say - we never - we never used to - spend a lot of money like in tripping. Nobody did in them days. No. We didn't.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4270034 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12201098\charrsid2837000 Can you tell me how you used to spend Saturdays in those days?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3486081 FP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12201098\charrsid2837000 What do you - after we'd left school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4270034 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12201098\charrsid2837000 What did you usually do on Saturday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3486081 FP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12201098\charrsid2837000 
Well we used to have cricket matches. And - that's how we used to spend our time. And we had to walk - we had to walk nearly - what - a place wh
at they used to call - in Yorkshire, Grasslea, I don't know how it come to get that name, but that's nearly up again Brierley fever hospital, piece of land there. We used to have to walk - we used to walk right up there, to have a game of cricket.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4270034 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12201098\charrsid2837000 These games weren't sort of organised by anybody?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3486081 FP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12201098\charrsid2837000 Oh no. No, we used to - ourselves. Mm. No, we used to -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4270034 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12201098\charrsid2837000 Did you do jobs too on Saturday, did you go and work for the butchers firm or did you help out your dad?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3486081 FP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12201098\charrsid2837000 Well when I get a bit - when I got a bit older I used to - like you know were helping }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid10446766\charrsid2837000 Kenyans}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12201098\charrsid2837000  like you know. 'Cos I was - I used to be delighted to see how - you know, think it were killing on it I used to like.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4270034 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12201098\charrsid2837000 On Sundays you went to church three times and you used to have different clothes for going to chapel?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3486081 FP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12201098\charrsid2837000 Just - special -
