And then we used to go to - we used to - have a walk round, you know, with three or four - mates of us. But our Ben, our Ben, he used to - he went - he left - Primitives and went to church. And I Walt -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4270034 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12201098\charrsid2837000 Your mum carried on going did she when the children broke off?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3486081 FP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12201098\charrsid2837000 Oh aye, she goes - she - carried on going to chapel - all her - all her - all her - 'til she lived. Yes.
\par 
