at's right, that's way her used to carry on in those days. Used to - you know - you could have - you could have plenty of help if you - but you - you know, you didn't want anybody - picking - poking about in your house, while - not when - 'cos there were 
plenty of us - to do little odd jobs like you know. Such as -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4270034 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12201098\charrsid2837000 The aunt that you mention then did she live nearby?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3486081 FP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12201098\charrsid2837000 Yes, well she just lived at Shafton, that was a mile away. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4270034 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12201098\charrsid2837000 Did you have lots of relatives that lived round about?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3486081 FP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12201098\charrsid2837000 Well no, not - really a lot. Might be just about - two, something like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4270034 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12201098\charrsid2837000 Did you see very much of them, you said that your mother used to go and visit, was this the one that your mother used to go and visit?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3486081 FP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12201098\charrsid2837000 Well - the - yes, she used to come 
regular, me mother - when of course she used to go across the fields and - to their house where they lived, it were nearest way, instead of going right away - down - towards Barnsley, then turn onto your right. For to go up Shafton, that were down again, 
Shafton Old School, what they call Shafton Green.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4270034 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12201098\charrsid2837000 You say they saw one another regularly, how regular was that, once a week?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3486081 FP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12201098\charrsid2837000 Oh sometimes twice a week, it just depends - barring - in the fruit time she - couldn't - manage it then. 'Course me aunt
ie used to come - then, she'd see if everything were all right, you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4270034 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12201098\charrsid2837000 Apart from relatives can you remember your parents having any other friends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3486081 FP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12201098\charrsid2837000 Oh - oh yes - she'd - plenty of friends. The best of it was - one - a big - a big friend of me
 mothers, and - she were land - landlady at Three Horseshoes at Brierley. And me mother never used to touch beer. Only she might just have a drink with me dad on a Sunday afternoon at dinner time when they used to fetch a - a pint of bear and pop it used 
to be and that were - that were threepence ha'penny, that were beer and pop. Of course - we never used to have to touch it. We'd to watch 'em.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4270034 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12201098\charrsid2837000 So you say your mum and dad had quite a lot of friends in the village?
